title: For Sale:  1945 ROF Enfield No. 5 Mk 1 "Jungle Carbine"
postcontent: Up for sale is a 1945 ROF Enfield No. 5 MK 1 Jungle Carbine chambered in .303 Brit.  These were used in the Pacific theater of WWII and also in the post-war colonial campaigns such as Malaysian Emergency.  This particular example was manufactured by the Royal Ordinance Factory (ROF) in 4/45.  The distributor tastefully refinished this rifle after import but there's just enough history left behind to tell this rifle's past.  Very strong rifling and a clean bore, which is rather unheard of for JC's as they were often used with corrosive ammo and in high humidity environments throughout Asia.  The handguard is a little loose, but otherwise a very nice example of a real Enfield Jungle Carbine.  This does qualify as a Curio & Relics (C&R) firearm.  $395 in a face to face transaction.  All IL laws followed, including FOID verification.  Feel free to ask questions.Sorry, no trades at this time.
